3) cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper uses compressive sensing techniques to develop the algorithm, which is a subfield of information theory. 
4) cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the computational complexity and memory requirements of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the domain of numerical analysis.
